import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from mpl_toolkits.mplot3d import Axes3D
from sklearn import cluster, metrics, decomposition


df = pd.DataFrame(pd.read_csv('201703_Taiwan_preprocessed.csv'))
df2 = df[(df['lon'] > 110) & (df['lat'] > 20) & (df['lat'] <25)]#only in Taiwan

In [2]:
df_location = df2.iloc[:,[8,9]].drop_duplicates()
silhouette_avgs = []
ks = range(2, 12)
for k in ks:
    kmeans_fit = cluster.KMeans(n_clusters = k).fit(df_location)
    cluster_labels = kmeans_fit.labels_
    silhouette_avg = metrics.silhouette_score(df_location, cluster_labels)
    silhouette_avgs.append(silhouette_avg)

# k = 2  10 
plt.bar(ks, silhouette_avgs)
plt.show()

In [3]:
plt.figure(figsize=(16, 12))
kmeans1 = cluster.KMeans(n_clusters = 3, random_state = 0)
%time kmeans1.fit(df_location)
plt.subplot(121)
plt.scatter(df_location['lon'].values, df_location['lat'].values, c=kmeans1.labels_)
plt.title('best')

kmeans2 = cluster.KMeans(n_clusters = 10, random_state = 0)
%time kmeans2.fit(df_location)
plt.subplot(122)
plt.scatter(df_location['lon'].values, df_location['lat'].values, c=kmeans2.labels_)
plt.title('worst')
plt.show()

silhouette_avg1 = metrics.silhouette_score(df_location, kmeans1.labels_)
print('best: ',silhouette_avg1)
silhouette_avg2 = metrics.silhouette_score(df_location, kmeans2.labels_)
print('worst: ',silhouette_avg2)

In [4]:
silhouette_avgs = []
ep = range(1, 10)
for e in ep:
    BDSCAN_fit = cluster.DBSCAN(eps = float(e/20), min_samples = 10).fit(df_location)
    cluster_labels = BDSCAN_fit.labels_
    silhouette_avg = metrics.silhouette_score(df_location, cluster_labels)
    silhouette_avgs.append(silhouette_avg)

# eps = 0.05  0.5 
plt.bar(ep, silhouette_avgs)
plt.show()

df3 = df2[(df2['Date']=='2017-03-10') & (df2['device_id']!='74DA38AF47C6')].iloc[:,[2,3,8,9]]
device = np.array(['' for _ in range(755)], dtype='U12')
air = np.zeros(shape=(144,755))
location = np.zeros(shape=(2,755))

for i in range(755):
    j = i*144
    device[i] = df3['device_id'].values[j]
    location[0][i] = df3['lat'].values[j]
    location[1][i] = df3['lon'].values[j]

for i in range(144):
    for j in range(755):
        air[i][j] = df3['PM2.5'].values[j*144+i]

df_temporal = pd.DataFrame({'device_id': device, 'lat': location[0], 'lon': location[1]})
for i in range(144):
    df_temporal['PM2.5_'+str(i)] = air[i]
df_temporal

In [17]:
num_cluster = range(2,10)
ami = []
nmi = []
for i in num_cluster:
    agglo = cluster.AgglomerativeClustering(n_clusters=i)
    agglo.fit(df_temporal.iloc[:,3:-1])
    labels_ori = agglo.labels_
    reduced_data = decomposition.PCA(n_components=9).fit_transform(df_temporal.iloc[:,3:-1])
    agglo.fit(reduced_data)
    labels_pca = agglo.labels_
    ami.append(metrics.adjusted_mutual_info_score(labels_ori, labels_pca))
    nmi.append(metrics.normalized_mutual_info_score(labels_ori, labels_pca))
    
plt.bar(num_cluster, ami, color='orange')
plt.show()
print(ami)
plt.bar(num_cluster, nmi)
plt.show()
print(nmi)

    reduced_data = decomposition.PCA(n_components=i).fit_transform(df_temporal.iloc[:,3:-1])
    agglo.fit(reduced_data)
    labels_pca = agglo.labels_
    ami.append(metrics.adjusted_mutual_info_score(labels_ori, labels_pca))
    nmi.append(metrics.normalized_mutual_info_score(labels_ori, labels_pca))
plt.bar(num_component, ami, color='orange')
plt.show()
print(ami)
plt.bar(num_component, nmi)
plt.show()
print(nmi)
